data.text:
You want to help others live healthier lives and make the world a better place. We get you. Take a big step in your healthcare career journey at Rosalind Franklin University. With a curriculum that centers on interprofessionalism, we prepare you for the future demands of healthcare fields. And you can find a place to belong within our inclusive campus community, which hosts 80-plus student organizations. Discover what the future holds for you at RFU.

Interprofessionalism brings together health specialists to achieve a single goal: serving patients more effectively through team-based care. At RFU, an interprofessional education means students from different colleges learn with — and from — each other. This prepares you to be part of interdisciplinary teams and develop a holistic view of patient care.
